    "narrative": "For LawDog today, the clear offensive centerpiece is **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite 83.34 efficiency score against Weiss. With a highly favorable 6.50 xERA opponent matchup and a wind-assisted venue, he is our must-start anchor. Alongside him, **Daulton Varsho** (72.31) and **Taylor Ward** (64.90) offer the highest upside. **Daulton Varsho** is particularly well-positioned; despite a slight penalty for the pitcher\u2019s ability to hold runners, he benefits from a weak 5.35 xERA starter and significant platoon leverage. **Taylor Ward** similarly secures a top-tier slot, bolstered by his lead-off spot and a strong platoon edge against Bubic. Meanwhile, **Gleyber Torres** and **Geraldo Perdomo** round out the top tier, with **Gleyber Torres** in particular capitalizing on a 13% boost from his platoon advantage.\n\nThe most difficult personnel decision centered on **Jonathan Aranda**, who was the final cut from our starting nine. While **Jonathan Aranda** posted a respectable 46.30, his matchup against the formidable Burns\u2014who maintains a 2.76 xERA\u2014pushed his efficiency below that of **Masyn Winn** and **Gavin Sheets**. We are also closely monitoring the weather in the game featuring **Luis Arraez**, **Matt Chapman**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Drew Gilbert**. The 42% rain risk creates notable volatility for that quartet; **Luis Arraez** and **Matt Chapman** retain starting roles due to their respective order positions and platoon advantages, but the risk of a rain-shortened outing is a legitimate concern for our total category accumulation. We will keep **Jonathan Aranda**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Drew Gilbert** on the bench, ready to pivot should any late-breaking lineup changes occur across the league.",
